Ensuring you take time to manage your own wellbeing and the wellbeing of those around you has never been more important. Some resources that may be useful: 

[DfE wellbeing hub](https://educationgovuk.sharepoint.com/sites/human-resources/SitePages/Wellbeing.aspx), which includes links to external services, including the Headspace App that is now free to all DfE employees, advice and support on self care, financial wellbeing, and information on internal sources of support such as Fair Treatment Ambassadors, Mental Health First Aiders and the Employee Assistance Programme. 

[Staff Networks](https://educationgovuk.sharepoint.com/sites/human-resources/SitePages/Staff-networks-and-groups.aspx): DfE have a variety of staff networks and groups for all employees to join, whether you identify yourself as someone who the network is aimed towards or if you just have an interest in diversity and inclusion matters. 

The Charity for Civil Servants [wellbeing hub](https://wellbeing.foryoubyyou.org.uk/?_ga=2.149852534.1714913557.1584627344-1204199371.1492766382), with a range of resources to support with stress, anxiety, resilience and depression. 

[NHS Every Mind Matters campaign](https://www.nhs.uk/every-mind-matters/), offering support and advice for individuals, parents and carers on mental health and wellbeing. 

[DfE wellbeing site](https://educationgovuk.sharepoint.com/sites/human-resources/SitePages/Health-and-wellbeing.aspx) 

[Employee Assistance Programme (EAP)](https://educationgovuk.sharepoint.com/sites/human-resources/SitePages/Employee-assistance.aspx) - (Available 24 hours a day, 365 days a year, EAP expert advice is here for you whenever you need - online and by telephone - giving you proactive, early access and intervention before issues get complex or to a point of crisis or ill health, username: dfewell, 0800 111 6387) 

[Mental Health First Aiders](https://educationgovuk.sharepoint.com/sites/lvewp00051) 

[Fair Treatment Ambassadors](https://educationgovuk.sharepoint.com/sites/human-resources/SitePages/Fair-treatment-ambassadors.aspx) 

[Anxiety UK](http://www.anxietyuk.org.uk/) or call 03444 775 774 

[Samaritans](http://www.samaritans.org/) or call 116123 
 
[DfE bereavement network](https://educationgovuk.sharepoint.com/sites/lveefa00003/SitePages/DfE-bereavement-network.aspx)  

[MIND](https://www.mind.org.uk/information-support/tips-for-everyday-living/loneliness/about-loneliness/) - provides advice, guidance and practical tips to manage loneliness and your mental health. 

[Clic](https://clic-uk.org/) - free online community supporting everyone with their mental health. 

[The Mix](https://www.themix.org.uk/) - free confidential help for under 25s. 

[Al-Anon](https://www.al-anonuk.org.uk/) - providing support to friends and family of problem drinkers. 

[NHS Mental Health HUB](https://www.nhs.uk/mental-health/) 

Silverline call 08004708090 - a free confidential telephone helpline offering information, friendship and advice to people over 55. 

[Mumsnet](https://www.mumsnet.com/) - a great place to connect with other parents and carers. 

[Gransnet](https://www.gransnet.com/) - a social networking site that offers a forum for over-50s to chat, debate, support each other and share a laugh. 

[Carers UK](https://www.carersuk.org/) - offering expert telephone advice via its support service. 

[NCT](https://www.nct.org.uk/) - offers a range of free, community-based activities and events across the UK, providing social connection and support for parents. 

[Ataloss](https://www.ataloss.org/) - if you have been bereaved and need support. 

[The Good Grief](https://www.thegoodgrieftrust.org/) - if you have been bereaved and need support. 

[Sudden](https://sudden.org/) - if you have been suddenly bereaved, Sudden can provide specialist support. 

[British Red Cross](https://www.redcross.org.uk/get-help/get-help-with-loneliness/wellbeing-support) - The British Red Cross's "Tackling Loneliness Digitally" programme has developed some new resources to help build confidence, coping skills and connections for adults and young people. 

[The Marmalade Trust](https://www.marmaladetrust.org/) - raising awareness of loneliness and helping people make new friendships. 

[Staying Safe](https://stayingsafe.net/) - provides information on how to make a safety plan, including video tutorials and online templates to guide you through the process. 

[SHOUT](https://www.giveusashout.org/) text 85258 or text YM if you're under 19 - speak to someone about how you are feeling. 

[Urgent NHS mental health services](https://www.nhs.uk/nhs-services/mental-health-services/where-to-get-urgent-help-for-mental-health/) - if you need help for a mental health crisis or emergency please seek immediate expert advice and assessment. Please dial 999 if someone's life is at risk i.e. if you or someone else are seriously hurt or have overdosed. 

[NHS psychological therapies service](https://www.nhs.uk/nhs-services/mental-health-services/where-to-get-urgent-help-for-mental-health/) - talking therapies or psychological therapies that are effective and confidential treatments delivered by fully trained and accredited NHS practitioners. 
